<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">heh i  had the same problem last year. i brought my grades up, wrote an official looking proposal, and sat and had a logical discussion with my dad. i now play everquest again. try talking calmly ang logicaly, present your arguement in a suitable and respectful fashion, and approach your dad as a "business partner" with whom to negotiate, not as a tyrant who took away your EQ. this wil be hard, but can be worth it. dont try to go behind his back cause if u get caught it's yer ass and no mo EQ fer sure! be calm, cool, and collective, and be sure to compromise. (you don't have to always be right ya know) -Ramaras Dirkspinner lvl 21 rogue and 16 year old Eq player</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
